  "text": "It seems that over-reductant amount encourages the \"Boudouard reaction\" to occur which retarded the direct reduction of mill scale, reaction [CITATION_1] . Also, by comparing the maximum iron recovery, it can be noticed that the maximum iron recovery obtained when using coke (76%) was lower than when using graphite (83%). This can be attributed, besides the effect of over-reductant, to the ash constituents in the coke. According to the literature [CITATION_2] the coke ash components such as silica, alumina, and silicates alter the reduction equilibrium.",
